Serves 8-10Ingredients:750ml (3 cups) milk250g (1 cup) butter125g (1 cup) semolina125g (1 cup) desiccated coconut200g (1 cup) sugar5ml (1 tsp) coarsely ground cardamom120g (1 cup) self-raising flour2.5ml ( tsp) baking powderTopping:2-3 drops cardamom essence250ml (1 cup) whipped cream, sweetenedAsha's Spice Box: A glossary of exotic Indian ingredientsMethod:1) Preheat oven to 180 C. Prepare a 23cm round baking pan with a non-stick spray.2) Heat milk and butter together until the butter melts. Remove from heat, stir in semolina, coconut, sugar and cardamom. Leave to cool.3) Sift in flour and baking powder. Mix well. Pour mixture into baking pan and bake for about 30 minutes. Remove and allow to cool.4) For the topping, stir the essence into the cream and spread over the cake with a spatula and serve.